Fair enough, the confusion was already there so it shouldn't be the responsibility of this PR to fix it. I've started [a Zulip discussion](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/.60sup.60.2F.60inf.60.20or.20.60max.60.2F.60min.60.20for.20set.20interval.20lemmas.3F) so we don't forget about cleaning this up.

Since the other results adjacent to this don't have `simp`, these probably shouldn't either.

In conclusion, looks good to me, let's get this merged!

bors r+
